ter%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20is%20struggling%20to%20maintain%20his%20authority%2C%20as%20politicians%20on%20both%20the%20left%20and%20the%20right%20of%20his%20Conservative%20Party%20are%20threatening%20to%20vote%20against%20his%20flagship%20asylum%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliament%20will%20hold%20a%20first%20vote%20on%20Tuesday%20on%20the%20legislation%20that%20would%20override%20some%20human%20rights%20law%20with%20the%20intention%20that%20this%20would%20allow%20the%20first%20deportation%20flights%20to%20leave%20for%20Rwanda%20before%20a%20national%20election%20expected%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20law%20is%20opposed%20by%20some%20moderate%20Conservative%20politicians%20who%20are%20worried%20about%20Britain%20breaching%20its%20human%20rights%20obligations%20and%20also%20by%20right-wing%20lawmakers%20who%20want%20the%20government%20to%20go%20further.%20Both%20sides%20are%20taking%20legal%20advice%20before%20deciding%20how%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Mr%20Sunak%2C%20struggling%20to%20revive%20a%20weak%20UK%20economy%20and%20heavily%20trailing%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20in%20opinion%20polls%2C%20the%20Rwanda%20policy%20has%20become%20the%20defining%20issue%20for%20his%20government%2C%20despite%20lawyers%20saying%20at%20every%20stage%20that%20it%20will%20not%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Rwanda%20policy%20has%20become%20a%20totemic%20struggle%20and%20it%20has%20liberated%20the%20factions%20in%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20to%20continue%20their%20all-out%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tony%20Travers%2C%20a%20politics%20professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20was%20ruled%20unlawful%20by%20the%20UK's%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20month%2C%20which%20said%20genuine%20refugees%20would%20be%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20returned%20to%20their%20home%20countries%20where%20they%20might%20face%20potential%20violence%20or%20ill-treatment%2C%20which%20would%20breach%20British%20and%20international%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20spent%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20billion%20pounds%20on%20the%20scheme%20in%20the%20hope%20it%20will%20deter%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20-%20including%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Iran%20and%20Iraq%20-%20who%20arrive%20on%20the%20south%20coast%20of%20England%20after%20crossing%20in%20small%20boats%20from%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sign%20of%20how%20uncertain%20Mr%20Sunak%20is%20about%20the%20size%20of%20any%20parliamentary%20rebellion%2C%20he%20decided%20against%20making%20it%20a%20confidence%20vote.%20If%20Sunak%20had%20done%20so%20and%20lost%2C%20he%20would%20have%20faced%20calls%20to%20hold%20a%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20prime%20minister%20stands%20to%20be%20badly%20weakened%20if%20he%20loses%20any%20vote%20on%20the%20legislation.%20Only%2029%20Conservative%20members%20of%20parliament%20would%20need%20to%20rebel%20to%20defeat%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20on%20Sunday%20if%20Mr%20Sunak%20would%20call%20a%20snap%20election%20if%20the%20legislation%20failed%20to%20pass%2C%20Michael%20Gove%2C%20a%20senior%20government%20minister%20in%20charge%20of%20regional%20development%20and%20housing%2C%20played%20down%20the%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we're%20not%20contemplating%20that%20because%20I'm%20confident%20that%20when%20people%20look%20at%20the%20legislation%20and%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20reflect%2C%20that%20they%20will%20recognise%20that%20this%20is%20a%20tough%20but%20also%20proportionate%20measure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Sky%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EDivisions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sunak%20finds%20himself%20in%20a%20similar%20crisis%20that%20engulfed%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20under%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Theresa%20May%20during%20the%202016-19%20fight%20to%20implement%20Brexit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%20a%20prime%20minister%20is%20facing%20a%20revolt%20from%20backbench%20members%20of%20parliament%2C%20there%20are%20rumours%20of%20colleagues%20plotting%20a%20leadership%20challenge%2C%20there%20are%20concerns%20about%20Britain%20abandoning%20its%20international%20promises%2C%20and%20questions%20about%20the%20power%20of%20parliament%20versus%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20Tuesday's%20vote%2C%20Mr%20Sunak%20will%20on%20Monday%20appear%20at%20the%20official%20COVID-19%20inquiry%20for%20a%20day-long%20hearing%20examining%20his%20role%20in%20response%20to%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sunak%2C%20who%20was%20finance%20minister%20at%20the%20time%2C%20has%20been%20accused%20by%20one%20former%20government%20adviser%20of%20saying%20the%20government%20should%20%26quot%3Bjust%20let%20people%20die%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20impose%20a%20lockdown%20because%20he%20was%20worried%20about%20the%20impact%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bigger%20danger%20for%20Sunak%20will%20come%20from%20the%20parliamentary%20battles%20over%20his%20Rwanda%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20lawmakers%20said%20that%20while%20they%20expected%20the%20government%20to%20win%20the%20vote%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20bigger%20showdown%20would%20come%20at%20the%20next%20stage%20when%20they%20can%20vote%20on%20amendments%20likely%20after%20Christmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20when%20the%20rebels%20will%20get%20stuck%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20Rishi%20Sunak-supporting%20Conservative%20member%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Conservative%20Party%20chairman%20Richard%20Holden%20underlined%20the%20threat%20to%20the%20government%20last%20week%20when%20he%20warned%20colleagues%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Binsanity%26quot%3B%20to%20oust%20Mr%20Sunak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBritain%20was%20once%20known%20for%20its%20stable%20politics.%20But%20if%20Sunak%20were%20to%20be%20toppled%2C%20the%20country%20would%20be%20on%20its%20sixth%20prime%20minister%20in%20just%20over%20seven%20years%20