hat%20delivered%20a%20landslide%20victory%20for%20the%20democracy%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20clampdown%20on%20dissent%20--%20aided%20by%20a%20sweeping%20national%20security%20law%20imposed%20by%20Beijing%20--%20has%20included%20a%20drive%20by%20authorities%20to%20weed%20out%20from%20public%20office%20anyone%20deemed%20politically%20disloyal%20after%20the%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunday's%20voting%20day%20stretched%20to%20midnight%20after%20a%20rare%2090-minute%20extension%20was%20granted%20following%20a%20failure%20in%20the%20digital%20system%20used%20to%20confirm%20voters'%20eligibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20extra%20time%2C%20the%20government's%20official%20website%20was%20updated%20on%20Monday%20morning%20to%20show%20a%20final%20turnout%20of%2027.54%20per%20cent%2C%20with%20just%20shy%20of%201.2%20million%20out%20of%204.3%20million%20registered%20electors%20having%20gone%20to%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20the%20lowest%20turnout%20rate%20since%20the%20city's%20handover%20to%20China%20was%2035.82%20per%20cent%2C%20recorded%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECity%20leader%20John%20Lee%20had%20thanked%20the%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%201%20million%26quot%3B%20voters%20at%20around%201%3A45%20am%20Monday%20(1745%20GMT%20Sunday)%20for%20coming%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20voting%20Sunday%2C%20he%20said%20this%20year's%20election%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20last%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle%20to%20implement%20the%20principle%20of%20patriots%20ruling%20Hong%20Kong%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20now%20on%2C%20the%20district%20councils%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20what%20they%20were%20in%20the%20past%20--%20which%20was%20a%20platform%20to%20destruct%20and%20reject%20the%20government's%20administration%2C%20to%20promote%20Hong%20Kong%20independence%20and%20to%20endanger%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said%20after%20he%20cast%20his%20ballot%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20new%20rules%20announced%20in%20May%2C%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20that%20could%20be%20directly%20elected%20was%20slashed%20from%20462%20to%2088%2C%20with%20the%20other%20382%20seats%20controlled%20by%20the%20city%20leader%2C%20government%20loyalists%20and%20rural%20landlords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECandidates%20were%20also%20required%20to%20seek%20nominations%20from%20three%20government-appointed%20committees%2C%20which%20effectively%20shut%20out%20all%20pro-democracy%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2070%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20candidates%20picked%20to%20run%20for%20the%20election%20were%20members%20of%20the%20nominating%20committees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20also%20acted%20swiftly%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20any%20sign%20of%20dissent%20on%20Sunday%2C%20arresting%20at%20least%20six%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20were%20activists%20from%20the%20League%20of%20Social%20Democrats%20--%20one%20of%20the%20city's%20last%20remaining%20opposition%20groups%20--%20which%20had%20planned%20to%20stage%20a%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20first%20accused%20the%20trio%20of%20%26quot%3Battempting%20to%20incite%20others%20to%20disrupt%20district%20council%20elections%26quot%3B%20and%20later%20passed%20them%20to%20the%20Independent%20Commission%20Against%20Corruption%20(ICAC)%20over%20suspicion%20of%20%26quot%3Binciting%20others%20not%20to%20vote%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20League%20called%20the%20arrest%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20ironic%20and%20ridiculous%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20the%20national%20security%20police%20arrested%20a%2077-year-old%20man%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Battempt%20to%20carry%20out%20seditious%20acts%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%2038-year-old%20man%20was%20charged%20on%20Tuesday%20for%20reposting%20a%20video%20of%20an%20overseas%20commentator%20that%20allegedly%20incited%20people%20to%20boycott%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDT