0suggests%20eliminating%2020%2C000%20to%2046%2C000%20barred%20owls%20in%20a%20single%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Fish%20and%20Wildlife%20Service%20has%20a%20strategy%20for%20owl%20preservation%3A%20kill%20some%20to%20safeguard%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fws.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2FFinal%2520draft%2520Barred%2520Owl%2520EIS.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20open%20for%20public%20commentary%20until%20early%202024%2C%20seeks%20to%20preserve%20the%20native%20population%20of%20northern%20spotted%20owls%20and%20California%20spotted%20owls.%20To%20do%20that%2C%20the%20agency%20suggests%20%26quot%3Blethally%20removing%20barred%20owls%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20course%20of%20several%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompetition%20from%20the%20non-native%20invasive%20barred%20owls%20has%20been%20identified%20as%20a%20primary%20threat%20to%20the%20northern%20spotted%20owl%20and%20a%20significant%20and%20increasing%20threat%20to%20the%20California%20spotted%20owl%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20proposal%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20barred%20owls%20are%20%26quot%3Bslightly%20larger%20and%20more%20aggressive%26quot%3B%20than%20spotted%20owls%2C%20according%20to%20the%20proposal.%20They%20threaten%20spotted%20owls%20by%20disrupting%20their%20nesting%20and%20competing%20for%20prey%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fws.gov%2Fproject%2Fbarred-owl-management%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BResearchers%20also%20have%20seen%20a%20few%20instances%20of%20barred%20owls%20interbreeding%20with%20or%20killing%20spotted%20owls.%20Because%20the%20spotted%20owl%20is%20already%20struggling%20due%20to%20its%20reduced%20habitat%2C%20the%20effect%20of%20the%20barred%20owl's%20presence%20is%20an%20added%20stressor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20service%20press%20release