0eat%20breakfast.%20Our%20mornings%20begin%20with%20some%20red%20or%20black%20tea.%20We%20eat%20lunch%20by%2010%20am%2C%20which%20gives%20the%20residents%2C%20mostly%20farmers%2C%20energy%20to%20work%20throughout%20the%20day.%20We%20have%20dinner%20by%205%20pm%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20eat%20a%20lot%20of%20meat%20as%20it%20gets%20very%20cold%20during%20winter.%20We%20save%20our%20meat%20and%20fish%20by%20smoking%20them.%20A%20typical%20meal%20includes%20rice%2C%20%3Cem%3Edal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meat%20or%20dried%20fish%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20vegetables%20available%20in%20our%20backyard%20(root%2C%20wild%2C%20leafy%20vegetables)%20with%20a%20side%20of%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E.%20We%20also%20dry%20vegetables%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20dishes%2C%20Nambie%20heroes%20ingredients%20grown%20in%20Meghalaya%20%E2%80%94%20like%20fiddlehead%20ferns%2C%20elephant%20apple%2C%20elephant%20foot%20yams%2C%20purple%20yams%2C%20Indian%20sorrel%2C%20fish%20mint%20leaves%2C%20%3Cem%3Esohiong%3C%2Fem%3E%20(blackberry)%2C%20%3Cem%3Esohplhang%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20root%20vegetable)%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20makes%20%3Cem%3Echutneys%3C%2Fem%3E%20using%20ingredients%20like%20brinjal%20and%20dry%20fish%2C%20fermented%20fish%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20dried%20roselle%20with%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Epura%20%3C%2Fem%3E(rice%20flour)%2C%20%3Cem%3Ejadoh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20%3Cem%3EKhasi%3C%2Fem%3E%20rice%20recipe)%2C%20beef%20trotter%20soup%2C%20muskmelon%20and%20pork%20gravy%20dish%2C%20and%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20was%20appreciated%20by%20many%2C%20she%20also%20faced%20vicious%20trolling%20and%20hate.%20Trolls%20ridiculed%20her%20for%20cooking%20outdoors%2C%20the%20food%20she%20cooked%2C%20and%20even%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20wore%20slippers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20some%20really%20harsh%20comments.%20People%20said%20things%20like%20%E2%80%9CYour%20food%20looks%20like%20dog%